de.mrapp.apriori.datastructure

Interface Sortable<DataStructureType,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    DataStructureType - The type of the data structure
    T - The type of the items, which are contained by the data structure
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrequentItemSets, RuleSet

    public interface Sortable<DataStructureType,T>
    Defines the interface, a data structure, which is sortable using Comparable or Sorting instances, must implement.
    Since:
    1.2.0

      DataStructureType sort(@Nullable java.util.Comparator<T> comparator)

    • Method Detail

      • sort

        @NotNull
DataStructureType sort(@Nullable
                                @Nullable java.util.Comparator<T> comparator)
        Sorts the items, which are contained by the data structure.
        Parameters:
        comparator - The comparator, which should be used, as an instance of the type Comparable or null, if the natural ordering should be used. It might be an instance of the class Sorting
        Returns:
        A new data structure, which contains the items in sorted order, as an instance of the generic type DataStructureType. The data structure may not be null
